physical_examinations.relevant_findings: The patient presented with multiple encapsulated lipomas on the abdominal wall, thighs, and extremities.
Postoperative examination indicated healing without complications; however, one aspiration for a left abdominal seroma was required post-surgery.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The abdominal wall lipomas were completely excised, and the cosmetic result was excellent postoperatively.
